<br>
Remember that with these type of pens you cannot push them. Pushing them causes the nib to bite into the paper and throw globs of ink around. You may even break the tip if your not careful. You're going to have to learn to always pull with them so if you have a tricky line you'll need to rotate the paper around. <p>Be well, do good work, and keep in touch. -Writer's Almanac NPR</p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#336699>- </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs>Polykarbon BBS</a><font color=#336699> - </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2>Photoshop and Art questions</a> <font color=#336699> - </font><a href="http://www.polykarbon.com">Polykarbon: Manga & Photoshop</a><font color=#336699> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM ARTS AD SCRIPT -->
